HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 158
BY REPRESENTATIVE BUTLER
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates Tuesday, April 28, 2026, as Louisiana 4-H
and Future Farmers of America (FFA) Day at the state capitol and commends the
state officers of the Louisiana 4-H and the Louisiana FFA Association
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Tuesday, April 28, 2026, as Louisiana 4-H and Future Farmers of America
3 (FFA) Day at the state capitol and commends the state officers of the Louisiana 4-H
4 and the Louisiana FFA Association.
5 WHEREAS, the Louisiana 4-H and the Louisiana FFA Association are two of the
6 largest youth leadership organizations in the state, empowering young people through
7 hands-on learning, service, and career development; and
8 WHEREAS, the Louisiana 4-H program is the youth development program of the
9 LSU AgCenter that engages young people in meaningful learning experiences that build
10 leadership, citizenship, and life skills across all sixty-four parishes; and
11 WHEREAS, the National FFA Organization prepares and trains students for
12 leadership and careers in the science, business, and technology of agriculture; and
13 WHEREAS, the FFA organization's motto, “Learning to Do, Doing to Learn, Earning
14 to Live, Living to Serve”, instills values that guide members in their personal and
15 professional development; and
16 WHEREAS, Louisiana 4-H and FFA members exemplify dedication, leadership,
17 integrity, and service to their schools, communities, and the state of Louisiana.
18 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
19 designate Tuesday, April 28, 2026, as Louisiana 4-H and FFA Day at the state capitol.
